text: Nadezhdinsky () is a rural locality (a khutor) in Ivano-Kuvalatsky Selsoviet, Zilairsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 140 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 67 km from Zilair, 12 km from Ivano-Kuvalat. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zilairsky District
title: Nadezhdinsky, Republic of Bashkortostan
